Package: badgecreatr
Title: Create Badges for Travis, Projectstatus Codecov.io Etc in Github Readme
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Roel M.", "Hogervorst", email ="hogervorst.rm@gmail.com", role = c("cre", "aut"))
Description: Tired of copy and pasting almost identical markdown for badges in
    every new R package that you create on Github? 
    This package will search for relevant information in your DESCRIPTION file
    and your 
    such as a .travis.yml file and if that one includes  and create the relevant badges in your 
    readme.rmd file. Currently creates badges for  Repostatus, licence
    'Travis' build status, 'codecov.io' code coverage, minimal R version, CRAN, 
    current version of your package and last change.
Depends:
    R (>= 3.2.4)
License: GPL-3
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
BugReports: https://github.com/RMHogervorst/badgecreatr/issues
Suggests:
    testthat
RoxygenNote: 5.0.1
Imports: 
    methods,
    stringr
